When you input a number using `scanf` with the `%d` format, then it reads an integer ***of any number of digits***. When you have the consecutives, `%d%d` then it will read two integers ***of any number of digits***. This is exactly what you&#39;re seeing.

If you want to read only a ***single*** digit for each integer, then you must specify `1` as the input (field) width! This will do what you want:

    scanf(&quot;%1d%1d&quot;, &amp;minx, &amp;x);

