Your problem could be caused by:
```
universe = Arrays.copyOf(nextGenWorld, nextGenWorld.length);
```

If I remember correctly, the array returned by Arrays.copyOf with objects is the same as the array provided. This is because the array you are using is of type Cell. Because Cell is not a primitive, instead of its value being duplicated into the new array, the object is copied into the new array.

In this case, you would probably want to:

1) Define a new array of Cells that has the same dimensions as the old one.

2) Iterate through the array of cells and make a new Cell at each index (and each cell in the new array would store the same information as in the first array).

Eg:
```
